Hi SBI Team,
 
Thanks for confirming the source/destination versions.
 
From a version compatibility perspective, GitLab project file export/import the source export should be from a version up to two minor versions behind the destination. Because 17.8.0-ee → 18.1.6-ee is outside that supported compatibility is not guaranteed.
 
On the assignee / creator mapping point, what you are seeing can be expected when the requirements for contribution mapping are not met during a file export/import migration to GitLab Self-Managed. 
 
The docs say that, to map users correctly, the following must be true:
 
The owner of the project’s top-level group should perform the export.
An administrator must perform the import.
The required users must already exist on the destination instance.
Users must have a public email on the source that matches their primary email on the destination.
 
The docs also state: “If any of the previous conditions are not met, user contributions are not mapped correctly. Instead, all GitLab user associations are changed to the user who performed the import.”
 
